node.text:
First in-depth look at the house we built in Montana. The house is 1248sq ft, 12’ walls, 6:12 roof, and overlooks our little lake.

Huge thanks to my amazing sponsor Ferguson Showrooms for providing the appliances, fixtures, and lighting.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Theron Humphrey on September 01, 2021. May be an image of body of water.

node.text:
I have to actively work daily at staying connected to my body. It’s so easy for me get honed in on doing, creating, building, producing that I detach to get it done…I am grateful I know myself a bit more in this season of life that I’m at least aware of what’s happening and can practice reconnecting with my body. ⁣
⁣
Water will forever be my happy place. My hole in the coming years is to be a strong voice in protecting this precious resource. ⁣
⁣
And! I wanted to thank everyone that has come through our Airbnb this year (link in bio if you’re looking for winter months or next year), my long term vision is to offer experiences and warm places to stay as a means of supporting our creative paths (vs buying a t-shirt kind of thing). Hope that makes sense ✨

node.text:
Sunday garage details (feat. Maddie the coonhound) ✨⁣
⁣
The garage / living space is mostly done! Sans trim (hello winter project) and appliances (I ordered 3 months ago and haven’t arrived 🥺)⁣
⁣
This build is no doubt attached to a childhood memories: some of my best days were working with my granddaddy in his shop & I feels like my generation really embraced that NYC / ‘Friends’ loft living idea…or at least we thought Andy Warhol and all those cats were doing something really neat. ⁣
⁣
It’s always in my mind to be transparent as possible with costs. It’s rad to see others incredible builds out in the world, on TV on IG, but I dislike that it’s some sort of big secret what things cost. I’m all about changing that. Housing is a need and I’m all for building quality structures at fair prices.⁣
⁣
Yet what I built for might be higher or lower than what you want to create. Every moment in building is quality decision. I’m choosing to do metal roof and siding, which is way more than shingles, but it’s a long term outlook. Anyhow! Including monthssss of sweat equity I’m in the space for $75k⁣
⁣
- 24 x 32’⁣
- Insulated mono slab foundation
- Ductless HVAC
- 12’ exterior walls + scissor trusses ⁣
- 10x12’ R18 garage door ⁣
- Windows! Up high for main house privacy 
- Sleeping loft / living room / 1 BA⁣
- Open flex space / workshop / garage ⁣
⁣
The free plans are on my website, in a combo file with the cabin, I hope they inspire you to build something good ✨

node.text:
Garage progress! Beyond stoked on this space, I can confirm it’s lovely in person. My neighbor is a retired welder and he helped bring my vision for the sleeping loft ladder + railing into reality with some basic 1 1/2” square tubing. Anyhow I’m feeling beyond proud and grateful today 🌵⁣
⁣
The kitchen cabinets are off the shelf shaker type from HD, as basic as it gets, but I think they look just fine. Counter tops will be white quartz that’s a left over piece from someone else’s big project (ie: a great deal). 
⁣
I’m still sharing these build plans for free on my website (link in bio). It’s takes a ton of effort to imagine and create a space so I hope they help with your own project ✨

node.text:
Designing and building my own house this past year was one of the most rewarding and exhausting experiences I’ve ever had in my 38 years. And now sitting here this morning, looking out over the lake with Maddie & Rome, it’s fun to peel back the layers of the building process in my mind and to know exactly what happened behind that drywall and how much work it took. I’m mostly rambling out this caption over a nice cup of coffee because I’ve closed this chapter in my story…my sense of purpose over the past year…and now I’m open and searching for what’s next. ⁣
⁣
Many out there are struggling to find and buy affordable housing, and I truly have no big answers and my only suggestions here in this caption are going to feel on the nose. Sometimes it’s just good to note things with a feather, that you see it. ⁣
⁣
In some ways I believe housing was underpriced for many years, it is a mind bending amount of physical work, logistics, planning, and you have to reach deep into your soul to find the drive to finish a build. ⁣
⁣
I see the future of home building being smaller spaces, smaller closets, less toys, better designs, and a home owner contributing all free time to the project. It likely will also include some sort of prefabrication in controlled factories but for now those methods are still expensive, at least per sq ft. ⁣
⁣
My story in this build is I lived in an unbuilt van with a mattress for months to make this happen. I spent weeks on air mattresses and cots setting up and breaking down my bed each morning to finish insulation, drywall, or flooring. It wasn’t fun. A lot of days were hot and nights cold, but I had to be realistic about what it would take to build a dream and ultimately what I had to sacrifice. ⁣
⁣
Like I said at the start of all these words I don’t really have any answers I just hope that if you have a dream you’re willing to be uncomfortable to see it through. It’s worth it. ✨

node.text:
Home ✨ It’s wild to have this lake out my front door, a spot to swim and connect with nature, and with all that I’m called to be a good steward of this water and protect it while we’re here. ⁣
⁣
That’s why thus summer I’ve partnered with @volvocars to help tell their story of #ForEveryonesSaftey, as they embark on the journey of not only making safe cars for us but also the planet long term. Head over to their IG page to learn more about their innovative and new vision #volvocars

node.text:
I have a few small giveaways coming up of lovely things I have left over from my house and cabin build, I suppose it’s just a small thank you for y’all following along this past year ✨⁣
⁣
First up is some (very) nice 2x12” FireClay glass tile in Wren color in a matte finish. I have 36sq ft left over, so maybe just enough for a neat back splash or accent. I’m sure you already have a brilliant idea ✨⁣
⁣
Leave a comment below on how/if you could use it and I’ll get it shipped in the continental US on my dime!
